# claude's notes

vulkan 1.4 features we now have access to but don't use yet:

- push descriptors (core 1.4): alternative for the per-pipeline uniform sets
  (set 1) — no descriptor pools/sets to manage, just vkCmdPushDescriptorSet at
  bake time. Would delete the per-pipeline descriptor pool TODO.
- maintenance4+: pipeline layouts allow VK_NULL_HANDLE holes in set layouts,
  relaxed subgroup ops, etc. Minor conveniences.
- per-frame GPU arena: built and scrapped 2026-07-15 — it forked storage
  buffers into a parallel model next to the uniform buffer objects. Growable
  SBOs landed inside the buffer object model instead (see below); don't
  revisit the arena unless upload counts actually become a problem.
- image render targets: done 2026-07-16. Renderer_CreateRenderTexture(w,h,
  sampler) makes a color-attachment texture in the bindless array (sampled
  like any texture); Renderer_CreateRenderPass(texture, order) makes a pass
  targeting it (own depth buffer, cleared to transparent black). Image
  passes bake before the swapchain pass in ascending order; explicit
  barriers do what vulkrap's subpass dependencies did (attachment write →
  fragment read). Follow-ups: remove_render_pass not ported (needs pipeline
  destroy + retire); render textures are fixed-size (no resize path); pass
  clear color is hardcoded per target type

deprioritized (current sync works fine, revisit if it grows hairier):

- synchronization2 (core 1.3): vkQueueSubmit2 + VkSemaphoreSubmitInfo give
  per-semaphore stage masks, and vkCmdPipelineBarrier2 puts stage+access in one
  struct. EndFrame's wait_semaphores/wait_stages arrays and the image layout
  transition barriers get clearer.
- timeline semaphores (core 1.2): one counter semaphore can replace the
  per-frame fence + binary semaphore sets. Also fixes the known debt where a
  failed frame leaves the transfer semaphore signaled (timeline waits don't
  consume signals).

texture path follow-ups:

- per-instance texture indices are live (2d_ssbo, done 2026-07-16): the 2d
  pipeline samples textures[nonuniformEXT(index)] per instance; colored
  quads sample a 1x1 white texture so every instance takes the same
  branch-free path (uv rect + alpha-source mask computed per instance)
- no mipmaps: sampler is clamped to maxLod 1.0 and upload creates 1 mip level;
  generate mips at upload (vkCmdBlitImage chain)
- sampler config is hardcoded (NEAREST mag / LINEAR min, repeat, aniso 16);
  expose filtering/addressing per sampler, e.g. sampler_config_t
- storage buffers grow on demand (done 2026-07-15): Set/Push doubles the cpu
  shadow, the per-frame buffers are rebuilt at bake (after the fence wait)
  and the old ones sit on a retire queue for MAX_FRAMES_IN_FLIGHT frames —
  same buffer object model as uniforms, growth is just a capacity policy.
  Uniforms stay fixed-cap: their buffers are referenced by descriptor sets
  written at pipeline creation, so swapping them means descriptor updates.
  The retire queue is also the building block for texture streaming later
- uniform buffers (set 1) could migrate into the global set model too; then
  every pipeline shares one layout and descriptor code exists in exactly one
  place

misc:

- drop the libm dependency: define HANDMADE_MATH_PROVIDE_MATH_FUNCTIONS and
  supply own HMM_SINF/HMM_COSF/HMM_TANF/HMM_ACOSF/HMM_SQRTF (natural home:
  core_math). That removes the last libm user, so m_dep in src/meson.build can
  go too. stb_image already avoids libm (STBI_NO_LINEAR/STBI_NO_HDR keep pow
  out) — don't lose those defines. sqrtf can be a single sse intrinsic
  (_mm_sqrt_ss); sin/cos/tan/acos need polynomial approximations, which games
  want anyway
- route stb_image allocations through an arena (STBI_MALLOC/STBI_REALLOC/
  STBI_FREE macros, or File_Read + stbi_load_from_memory to at least keep file
  io in the arena)
- setup_physical_device picks the first 1.4-capable device; still needs the
  queue family / extension / feature / swapchain support checks from the TODO
  there, now including the Vulkan12Features descriptor indexing bits +
  bufferDeviceAddress, Vulkan13Features dynamicRendering and Vulkan14Features
  hostImageCopy
- image.c is the only engine file including stb; keep it that way so the
  stb_inc meson include stays engine-private
